00:17:11,717 --> 00:17:14,380
I think Surly Brewing sponsors Minneapolis,

416
00:17:14,380 --> 00:17:17,923
and Not Your Father's Root Beer sponsors Killer Queen Events in Portland.

417
00:17:20,769 --> 00:17:23,311
Before you actually pitch a sponsor for an event,

418
00:17:23,311 --> 00:17:25,113
here's some things you probably want to think about.

419
00:17:25,113 --> 00:17:26,974
How much control do you want to have

420
00:17:26,974 --> 00:17:28,876
over the portrayal of your game?

421
00:17:28,876 --> 00:17:30,497
How do you think the community will react?

422
00:17:30,497 --> 00:17:32,679
Is that something that's actually important for you?

423
00:17:32,679 --> 00:17:35,681
Are you now sanctioning official events yourself?

424
00:17:35,681 --> 00:17:37,503
And can there only be one event?

425
00:17:37,503 --> 00:17:39,244
What does that mean for non-sanctioned events?

426
00:17:39,244 --> 00:17:41,046
Are you, the game's creators,

427
00:17:41,046 --> 00:17:43,067
the only ones able to seek out sponsorships now?

428
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:45,289
And what does an agreement look like

