and food and beverage when the players come to play.

602
00:24:46,742 --> 00:24:50,283
So yeah, if you're indie, be nimble with your community

603
00:24:50,283 --> 00:24:52,744
and be personable and authentic to your game.

604
00:24:52,744 --> 00:24:54,725
To an extent, you can respond to and work

605
00:24:54,725 --> 00:24:57,026
with your communities in ways that the bigger studios can't.

606
00:24:57,026 --> 00:25:00,327
The community can be very forgiving of your mistakes

607
00:25:00,327 --> 00:25:02,888
if you show the effort of trying to make the game better.

608
00:25:02,888 --> 00:25:04,528
Be clever about how you do things

609
00:25:04,528 --> 00:25:06,029
and don't take no for an answer.

610
00:25:06,029 --> 00:25:08,150
Move fast because the big boys can't

611
00:25:08,150 --> 00:25:09,630
and don't let anything hold you back.

612
00:25:10,378 --> 00:25:14,640
If you're a larger company and studio and watching this talk, engage with your community

613
00:25:14,640 --> 00:25:16,401
and empower them and celebrate them.

614
00:25:16,401 --> 00:25:20,543
Learn about what they really want and really need because you may have more noise to deal

615
00:25:20,543 --> 00:25:23,505
with with a larger community than us as an indie.

616
00:25:23,505 --> 00:25:26,487
Experiment with your game and listen to the community and build goodwill.

